                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/629.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Garrett</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Nuevo Laredo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>By order of General Luis Caballero, military governor of Tamaulipas, 19,300
                    pesos, Villista currency, was taken from José Pereda, a <pb facs="1159" n="1043"
                        xml:id="pg_1043"/> Spanish merchant of Monterey, by military authorities
                    here to-day. Department can take such action as they deem appropriate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
